      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and 315 hp. The drivetrain is anchored by a G96 6-speed manual transaxle providing short, precise throws. Notably, the IMS bearing has been addressed with an LN Engineering retrofit, and the rear main seal was replaced concurrently. The chassis utilizes MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear suspension for optimized kinematics and lateral stability. Stopping power is provided by four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers over cross-drilled rotors. While the finish shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical components are dialed in, with the engine showing strong compression and no bore scoring issues. A purist-spec driver's car with the most critical preventative maintenance already completed.",
      "price": 32500.0,
